name: Latin America Meets Silicon Valley on Payments
short_description: We will talk about why Latin America is challenging from a payments perspective and identify particular opportunities for innovation.
venue_address: 1901 Harrison Street, 4th Floor “El Capitan” Conference Room, Oakland, CA
description:
Latin America: Local payments for an international community

Latin America offers huge opportunities in payments innovation. Despite recession in Brazil, Argentina, and Venezuela and meager GDP growth in Mexico, Colombia and Chile, e-commerce and emerging payments are growing rapidly, from 15%-40% per year depending on the market. With rapid growth for a least five more years, a large unbanked population and expanding penetration of smartphones, the digital transformation has arrived in Latin America’s payments industry.

Yet considerable challenges remain for payment players and merchants in Latin America. The use of cash payment methods, local credit card networks, complicated installment plans, and an opaque yet complex regulatory environment make billing customers a challenge at best and a complete quagmire at worst. Growing competition in the e-commerce enablement space means payment processors must constantly improve their offerings to remain relevant. Companies without a local strategy will perform poorly. As growth returns to the region in 2017, payment players and merchants must be ready to embrace rapid changes.

In our panel, Latin America: Local payments for an international community, we will cover why Latin America is challenging from a payments perspective and identify particular opportunities for innovation. Our panel of e-commerce payment processors and merchants will share insights on how to develop a local payments strategy.

name: UCD2016 Conference Being Human
short_description: Exploring the philosophical tension between humanity and science in post-digital world
venue_address: Deans Mews, 11-13 Cavendish Square, London W1G 0AN
description:
Being Human
At this year’s UCD Conference, we’ll be exploring the philosophical tension between humanity and science in post-digital, networked civilizations; what does it mean to be human in our new global digital community, and how do we design for our evolving species?

We’ll be hearing from the people who are bringing tomorrow to life – and bringing life to tomorrow – though the Internet of things, ambient intelligence, big data, sympathetic machines, hyper personalisation, social science, robotics, new applications for simulated worlds, virtual reality, service design, artificial intelligence, gaming, cryptocurrency, human behaviour analysis, computer vision, security, automation, simulated worlds, digital content and engagement, machine learning, biohacking, and the future of defense, flight, energy, social good, civil disobedience, cities, media, cars, commerce, health, finance, the global poor…

Come and meet scientists, technologists, and philosophers; and also designers, disruptors, and activists. Talk to people who are inventing new ways for technology to fill the gaps in our world; people who create digital solutions (and – yes – robots) to provide services that the infrastructure of our society is unable to provide.

Beyond the debate about the rise of the machines vs. the fall of humanity, be prepared to confront your own digital behavior – there’s no reward without risk at UCD! – and to come away with a new sense of awe and insight into the high-stakes game of designing technology for humanity.

Join the agitators, the innovators, and the rule breakers at #UCD16.

name: Crypto-Currencies - What is Coming?
short_description: In this session, we will retrace how we got where we are, what the status is in crypto-currencies & where we are going in the industry.
description:
If you have been following BayPay for the last several years, you know that we have been very active on the Bitcoin, Crypto-currency and Blockchain fronts. We even sponsored the first Bitcoin Summit organized by the Bitcoin Foundation in May 2013 at the Convention Center in San Jose. It was a very interesting experience at the time with the Winklevoss Twins on stage, with panels of investors and a strong lineup of entrepreneurs working hard to create a new world and eliminate friction in P2P transactions, micro-payments and international payments.

 

After several waves that saw the rise of the Bitcoin up to $1,200, the fear of many financial institutions and regulatory bodies around the world, many investments long forgotten and gone, the fall of the Bitcoin down to $170 and its rise again around $600 today, we want to revisit this topic and better understand where we are.

 

Far from being dead, the Bitcoin is still there and is the most traded crypto-currency in volume even if other currencies were created by companies like Ethereum, Ripple, etc. The Blockchain seems to take over with many applications (it will be the subject of another event later) as our last event “Can the Blockchain survive without Bitcoin” on Feb 18, 2016 illustrated (Video available for purchase or free to Online members at https://www.baypayforum.com/021816).

 

In this session, we will retrace how we got where we are, what the status is, in crypto-currencies and where we are going with executives in the industry who will share their experience and opinions.

 

We look forward to seeing you for an evening of education on the topic and networking with peers.

short_description: Gartner BI & AS will help you develop a "short list" of technology and service providers who can meet your particular needs.
description:
Analytics Leadership: Empowerment without Anarchy
For a company to be successful with analytics, it takes more than a single leader. Analytics requires an abundance of astute leaders distributed throughout an organization working to apply just the right technology and skill sets to their business domain.   

Join us for Gartner Business Intelligence & Analytics Summit 2016 and gain the analytics leadership you need to empower users to be autonomous without creating a state of disorder.

name: JAX London 2016
short_description: JAX London is the Conference for Java & Software Innovation.
description: JAX London is a three-day conference for cutting-edge software engineers and enterprise-level professionals. JAX brings together the world’s leading innovators in the fields of JAVA, microservices, continuous delivery and DevOps.

name: Next: Economy Summit
short_description: Be part of the discussion and understand how the technological revolution will shape the future of work and business.
description:
The Next:Economy Summit aims to help businesses, policy makers, and technologists to chart a course from the WTF economy we experience today, full of wonders and horrors in equal measure, to a Next Economy that brings prosperity to all.

This is an executive-style conference, featuring frank conversations with business leaders shaping the Next Economy.

name: Pubcon Las Vegas 2016
short_description: Pubcon is the premier social media and optimization conference and expo, will hold its multi-track Las Vegas event on October 10–13, 2016.
venue_name: Las Vegas Convention Center South Halls
description:
Pubcon, the premier social media and optimization conference and expo, will hold its multi-track Las Vegas event on October 10 – 13, 2016 at the Las Vegas Convention Center South Halls in the sunny entertainment capital of the world.

October 10 will feature a full day of their optional Pubcon Masters Group search and social media training, with the official Pubcon Las Vegas 2016 conference taking place on October 11 – 13, and the exhibition hall scheduled to be open on October 11 – 12.

Pubcon Las Vegas 2016 — named a Forbes must-attend conference and an Inc. top conference for growing your business — features the industry’s leading businesses, start-ups, speakers, keynotes, exhibitors, and sponsors involved in social media, digital marketing, search engines, and online advertising, and will offer a week-long look at the future of technology presented by a vast array of the world’s top innovators, along with being the exclusive host to the fourth annual U.S. Search Awards.

Pubcon Las Vegas 2016 will be among the strongest gatherings of search and social ever assembled, offering an unrivaled highly-productive conference experience at some of the fairest cost-effective rates in the industry, and with the leading technology and online marketing visionaries who will be in Las Vegas, they are confident that every attendee will come away with valuable new ideas and solutions for their businesses.

Pubcon truly starts where other social media and digital marketing conferences end, and during their Las Vegas conference in October 2016 a collective and invaluable vision for the future will be presented by a virtual who’s who of technology. Join thousands of leading social media, optimization, and online marketing professionals from around the world for Pubcon Las Vegas 2016, and learn more about their event with the information on this page, including the following Pubcon video.
event_roles: Conference, Expo, Meetup, Class, Networking, Other

name: TechWeek New York 2016
short_description: Tech Week New York 2016
description:
Techweek is back to New York for its 4th year; and we couldn’t be more excited. Techweek New York launched in 2013 with a small and intimate attendee list of 500, while this year we are anticipating thousands. 

Techweek New York isn’t your typical technology conference experience.  We are on a mission to support technology ecosystems – to bring together people, ideas, and resources to ensure local technology ecosystems are enriched and develop. And we take this mission very seriously. Techweek New York 2016 happens over a week, and it happens in multiple locations: highlighting some of the headquarters, in-office charms, and culture of New York’s emerging technology greats; and some of its very much emerged technology businesses too.  New York, get ready – we’re coming back.

name: GMIC Taipei 2016
short_description: GMIC Taipei is a platform for technology innovators, thought leaders and experts to connect across industries.

name: IdeaLab! 2016
short_description: Europe's leading student run founders' conference. Every year at WHU - Otto Beisheim School of Management.
venue_name: WHU - Otto Beisheim School of Management
description:
They are very happy to host IdeaLab! The Founders’ Conference at their university WHU – Otto Beisheim School of Management in Vallendar, Germany. Vallendar is a lovely little town near the city of Koblenz.

It has been made a great place to stay by the people who live and study there and they can assure you that you will have a great time here!

Their IdeaLab! family is a very important part in organizing and hosting the conference. They are eight brothers and two sisters organizing the conference next year and are greatly supported by their elder siblings who organized IdeaLab! 2015 and 2014.

name: New York Comic Con 2016
short_description: New York Comic Con is the East Coast's biggest and most exciting popular culture convention.
venue_address: Eleventh Avenue, between 34th and 40th streets, in Hell's Kitchen
description: New York Comic Con is the East Coast's biggest and most exciting popular culture convention. Their Show Floor plays host to the latest and greatest in comics, graphic novels, anime, manga, video games, toys, movies and television. Their panels and autograph sessions give Fans a chance to interact with their favorite creators. Their screening rooms feature sneak peeks at films and television shows months before they hit either big or small screens. And with dedicated professional hours, New York Comic Con is a market place, bringing together the major players in the entertainment industry. New York Comic Con is the second largest pop culture convention in America and the only one that takes place in the comic book, publishing, media and licensing capital of the world — Gotham City.

name: 0100 Conference Nordics, 5th October 2016, Copenhagen
short_description: We provide the perfect platform for Limited Partners and General Partners to network, share knowledge and find their next Venture partner.
description: We are a new generation conference company specializing in high-profile, networking type meetings for the key players in the VC ecosystem. Our goal is to provide you with a platform to facilitate knowledge sharing and to ultimately maximize  your opportunity of finding your next venture partner. Its  a unique chance for you to meet all these thought leaders under one, single roof. For this Nordic conference we are expecting 200+ senior attendees along several LPs and leading VCs.

name: London Venture Capital World Summit 2016
short_description: The Premiere Venture Capital Event of The Year! This one day distinguished finance event that will bring together Innovators
description:
Venture Capital World Summit Ltd is now an investment company, as it has now invested on an upcoming business start-up (30% equity) based in the Netherlands with global potential (more details will be unveiled at the event).

The Venture Capital World Summit , is an international event promoting a wealth of opportunities from representatives from International Funds and Technology, including Entrepreneurship, Business growth and Sustainable Social Innovation.

The benefit of attending the event is that you will meet many delegates that will attend this memorable summit event. Resulting, in more business being achieved for you, from this exposure including speakers that will convey important and breakthrough messages and by demonstrating expertise and insights on a global stage of operations.

name: Mondial Innovation Forum
short_description: Mondial Innovation Forum is an invitation-only conference focused on the future of the car industry taking place on October 5th in Paris.
venue_address: 1 Place de la Porte de Versailles
description:
Mondial Innovation Forum is an invitation-only conference focused on the future of the car industry taking place on October 5th in Paris.


Organised by the Mondial de l’Automobile (Paris Motor Show) in association with Startup Sesame and Connectors, the Mondial Innovation Forum is a new invitation-only conference focused on the future of the car industry that brings together 300 decision makers, industry innovators, startup founders and investors. The conference program explores the theme of “Moving Beyond Cars” with a focus on the technological, economic and social impacts of disruption.


Startup Sesame Mobility hosts the pitch competition at the Mondial Innovation Forum in October 5th. It will be the finals of the international call for entries where the top 8 applicants will present their project in front of a jury of experts and investors.


Startup Sesame Mobility is dedicated to the mobility challenges of the future and provide selected entrepreneurs to unparalleled access to the conferences and events where their business will grow. The program trains founders in event strategy, B2B networking and connect them with a network of Tech events and mentors.

name: NoVA TechBreakfast featuring awesome tech demos
short_description: Come to the NoVA TechBreakfast on Oct 5 featuring awesome tech companies http://bit.ly/1MA2wCO
description: Interact with your peers in a monthly morning breakfast meetup. At this monthly breakfast get-together techies, developers, designers, and entrepreneurs share learn from their peers through show and tell show-case style presentations. And yes, this is free! Thank our sponsors when you see them. This edition at AOL HQ - Dulles features demos from 4 awesome tech companies Find out more and RSVP at http://bit.ly/1MA2wCO

name: Smart Kitchen Summit
short_description: The first and only event looking at the future of the way we shop, store, prepare and cook our food.
description:
The way we cook, eat, buy, store and interact around our food is undergoing radical change. At the Smart Kitchen Summit, you'll meet with the visionaries in the culinary, smart home, appliance, commerce and fitness disciplines creating the future of the most important room in the house.

The Summit will open with a reception on October 5th with a showcase of products from companies creating and innovating and the bleeding edge of cooking, kitchen and food.  On October 6th, attendees will be able to hear from the leading voices in the connected kitchen and foodtech space. Speakers such as Nathan Myhrvold, Charlie Kindel, Chris Young, Bill Mitchell and many more. Join us!

name: South Summit
short_description: The South Summit is one of the leading startup conferences in Europe aimed to prove to the world the talent, the innovation.
description:
The South Summit's mission is to gather the greatest innovations from Southern Europe & Latam and connect them to some of the regions’ largest customers and investors. They do this through The South Summit, an annual gathering of Southern Europe and Latam´s top talent. With more than 7.000 attendees, including 3.500 entrepreneurs and 450 investors The South Summit has become one of Europe’s most relevant startup up events.

This started from humble beginnings in 2012 when their Founder María Benjumea decided to empower the entrepreneur ecosystem fostering relationships between Startups, Corporations and Investors creating Spain Startup & Investor Summit (SSIS).

name: 2016 National Angel Summit
short_description: Scaling Up Angel Capital to Drive Canadian Innovation
registration_details: Click here to register, and to find out more about NACO's 2016 Summit!
venue_address: 1128 W Hastings St. Vancouver, British Columbia V6E 4R5, Canada
description:
Angel Investors, industry partners, supporters, as well as startup founders from across Canada and internationally, are invited to join us for our National NACO Summit taking place in Vancouver October 4-6, 2016. This will be our largest event to date with an anticipated 400 delegates from across the investor ecosystem in attendance. Our International guests are invited to join us at a special networking reception on Monday, October 3.

This year's conference program will be a blend of NACO Academy workshops, panels, keynote presentations, round table discussions, sector focused tours, networking activities, our Awards Gala and Startup Pitch Competition. NACO will bring together experts across a broad range of topics and geographies, while mixing in refreshing opportunities to grow networks and business opportunities.

We will kick off the official conference program with a Boat Cruise Reception taking in Vancouver's breathtaking harbour views. New this year are our industry sector tours focused on some of Vancouver's hottest emerging tech startups, as well as some activity experiences to foster both networking and learning, while taking advantage of the best that Vancouver is known for: mountains, parks and craft beer!
